#Text=The Philadelphia 76ers ( 5 - 37 ) blew out the Portland Trail Blazers ( 18 - 25 ) on Saturday , 114 - 89 .
#Text=This was easily the Sixers best performance of the season , as they took care of business against a hot Portland team .
#Text=The game got our of hand early , as Philadelphia carried a 25 - point lead into halftime .
#Text=Almost everything was clicking tonight for Philly , as the Sixers outshot the Blazers by 17 percent while also outrebounding , outassisting , and tying in the turnover battle .
#Text=It 's games likes these that give Sixers fans some hope for the future and this looks like a completely different team with Ish Smith in the fold .
#Text=Portland was playing in the second half of a back - to - back here and it was clearly evident through their poor play .

#Text=Damian Lillard and C.J McCollum have been carrying this team all year , but the two combined to shoot 10 - for - 36 from the field while accumulating just 27 points , four rebounds and four assists .
#Text=No player on this team had more than 14 points , seven rebounds or five assists and that 's a bad sign for success .
#Text=The Blazers shot just 39 percent from the field and this will be one of those games they 'd just like to get on the plane and forget forever .
#Text=Portland will look to play better on Monday against the Washington Wizards in their next fixture .
#Text=This Philadelphia team has been playing much better since the acquisition of Ish Smith and this performance emphasizes that fact .
#Text=This Sixers team at the beginning of the season would have had no chance to beat a team by 25 points and this is a great sign going forward .
#Text=Five different players scored at least 14 points tonight for Philly with all five combining to shoot over 50 percent from the field in the win .
#Text=Jahlil Okafor was their best player tonight though , as he finished with 25 points and 10 rebounds .
#Text=Nerlens Noel 's four - point , eight - rebound line doesn’t look great , but his four blocks and four steals were a huge game changer tonight .
#Text=Richaun Holmes also had a nice game off the bench in garbage time , as he tallied 14 points and six rebounds .
#Text=The 76ers will look to build off this dominating win when they take on the New York Knicks on Monday .
